CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 28, 1941, pg. 3, reads: "Kay Club Celebrates Ten Years Of Progress - The Kay Boys' Club of Pittsburgh is one of the city's outstanding social agencies.  Hundreds of boys are shown the right road to travel under capable supervision at the club and later become model citizens.  The Kay Club is doing much to encourage good citizenship and patriotism.  Pictured above are some of the youngsters and officials who participate in programs sponsored by the Kay Boys' Club...In the other picture are the members of the Kay Club staff who direct the activities of the young members.  Sitting, left to right; Mrs. Minnie Philips, Mrs. Sue Coresy, Mrs. Gladys Howell, Standing, Richard Dickson, At...Thomas, Samuel Price, Everett Utterback, Malvin Goode of the YMCA and James Robinson. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, seated from left: Minnie Philips, Sue Coresy, Gladys Howell; standing: Richard Dickson, Mr. Thomas, Samuel Price, Everett Utterback Sr., Malvin "Mal" Goode, and James Robinson, gathered in Kay Boys' Club
